==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Episternum
<hw>Ep`i*ster"num</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Episterna</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Epi-</er>, and <er>Sternum</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A median bone connected with the
sternum, in many vertebrates; the interclavicle.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Same as <er>Epiplastron</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>One of the lateral pieces
next to the sternum in the thorax of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epistilbite</ent>⟦br⟧
